dogecoin.text:
During the 2021 bull run, major platforms like Coinbase Pro listed Dogecoin, attracting a cult following and a new wave of mainstream attention.

More people were “going to the moon” with DOGE!

Right after Musk’s tweet, Dogecoin’s market cap hit $400 million, and crypto exchange Huobi quickly listed it.

This wasn’t just hype—Dogecoin’s lower fees and fast transactions gave it utility. It became the “people’s coin,” accessible to anyone.

Unlike Bitcoin, Dogecoin uses the Scrypt algorithm, making mining faster and less energy-intensive.

With a block time of 1 minute (vs. Bitcoin’s 10), Dogecoin enables faster transactions, contributing to its popularity for tipping and micro-payments.
